(1323, 'Padcev', NULL, 'Urothelial', 'NO', '12/19/2019 The FDA granted accelerated approval to Padcev (enfortumab vedotin-ejfv), a Nectin-4-directed antibody and microtubule inhibitor conjugate, meaning the drug specifically targets cancer cells â€“ in urothelial cancers. Padcev is indicated for the treatment of adult patients with locally advanced or metastatic urothelial cancer who have previously received a PD-L1 inhibitor and a platinum-containing chemotherapy. Padcev represents a new type of therapy for patients with advanced urothelial cancer whose disease has progressed on chemotherapy and immunotherapy.', 'enfortumab vedotin-ejfv', 'Bladder', NULL, NULL, 'Chemotherapy', 'antibody and microtubule inhibitor conjugate'),
